-- OTP Bank Falls for Second Day, Leading Hungarian Shares Lower
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-06-21T07:25:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-21/otp-bank-falls-for-second-day-leading-hungarian-shares-lower.html
OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP) , Hungary’s largest
lender, fell for a second day, leading a drop in the country’s
shares as a cut in the Federal Reserve’s growth estimates for
the U.S. deepened concern the global economy is slowing.  OTP’s shares dropped 2.3 percent to 3,684 forint by 9:18
a.m. in Budapest. The benchmark BUX stock index slid 1.4 percent
to 17,536.97.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
